@oliverbrian @CraigVodnik  Thank you.   The letters and pictures are truly amazing.  This scratched the surface.
28/ Thank you to #pfcDownen and my grandmother, Margaret Downen.   I love you both.  And thank you to all who served.  #VeteransDay
27/ He scrambled for pens and paper at every turn to write a letter and reassure her during troubling times.   #pfcDownen
26/ Their letters are the purest love story I have ever known.  She sustained him with words and supplies. #pfcDownen
25/ "I wish I could tell you how anxious and glad I will be to resume living with such a swell little wife once more." Nov 1945 #pfcDownen
24/  Married 73 years, #pfcDownen is now 98 and his wife, my grandma, is 93. http://t.co/CCYesJxTCW
23/ Thank you to everyone who makes Honor Flight possible.  #pfcDownen flew to DC in 2011 at age 94. http://t.co/5XC4TcZVKH
22/ #pfcDownen served his country well.  Here he is with his medals, including the Purple Heart. #pfcDownen http://t.co/FR9ok9al7l
21/ Reunited with his wife and daughter, they took a family trip to the Smoky Mtns and Florida.  #pfcDownen http://t.co/PstD4mJvjM
20/ #pfcDownen left France June 6, 1945 on a boat for the U.S., arriving Newport News June 18.   Discharged Oct 26, 1945.
19/ "The Chief of Staff of the Army directs me to inform you that your husband #pfcDownen is being returned to the U.S." #pfcDownen
18/ "The Secretary of War desires me to inform you that your husband #pfcDownen was returned to military control."  June 1, 1945
17/ "Would like to get back to the only country I could be satisfied in.  Turned down pass to England to get back to Indiana" #pfcDownen
16/ Liberated May 1945.  "I am the happiest man possible and get a lump in my throat at the thought of being home very shortly." #pfcDownen
15/ Jan 1945 from POW camp: "Well in a few hours a very nice daughter will be another year older. Wish I was there.  I am fine" #pfcDownen
14/ He rode in a box car for 4 days without food or water.  Slept standing up to stay warm as others died. #pfcDownen http://t.co/lbmSoUSGC8
13/ Postcard from Stalag 4-B received March 30.  "I never lost hope that he was alive."  Captured 12/8 #pfcDownen http://t.co/ETqNVPRg7M
12/ "The Secretary of War expresses regret that your husband has been Missing In Action since 12/2 in France". #pfcDownen
11/ "Thanks for the Cokes and peanuts sure were good. So was stick candy, olives, apple juice and cookies and gum" November 1944 #pfcDownen
12/ Sept 1944  Near the Alps.  Cold at night.  Very hungry. Went to Church. "I am with you every day between our letters". #pfcDownen
10/ "We are in Italy.  We are closer to the front but still way back so don't you worry dear." July 1944 #pfcDownen http://t.co/dtX292ehLX
10/ "On cloud 9. 16 letters came today.  Was pleased that your mother wrote 'Dear Son'. Hope I can stay in food inspection".  #pfcDownen
9/ June 1944.  Northern Africa. "Not much going on but its one less day in a more dangerous region. May be going to Italy" #pfcDownen
8/ Grandma visited base in MS April 1944. Housing shortage so he lived in a garage.  Landlady brought biscuits.  Deploying soon. #pfcDownen
7/ They took a family picture during Thanksgiving leave in 1943.  That cute little girl...is my mom. #pfcDownen http://t.co/QhnhtcQbEM
6/ Had a swell letter from home today and it was most welcome. Nothing cheers me more than your letters.  #pfcDownen http://t.co/c90v6LxZMJ
5/ Air raid practice tonight with our gas masks on. Practicing bayonets and studying pistols.   May 1943 #pfcDownen http://t.co/MrEexel9eq
4/ "Thanks for the package of pens and ink.  Typhoid and tetanus shots today. Fatigues and gas mask."  April '43 #pfcDownen
3/ "This was the saddest day of my life up to present time but I will do my little bit to protect our wonderful life" Mar 1943 #pfcDownen
2/ His daughter was two months old.  He and his wife exchanged hundreds of letters over the next 2.5 years.  Will tweet excerpts #pfcDownen
1/ Meet Pfc. Carl Downen.  Drafted Dec 1942. Left for basic training March 1943 after 90 day deferment. http://t.co/wMSkiU3bPG
